HEADWORD: mud cat
<hw>mud cat</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A large
catfish (<spn>Pylodictus olivaris</spn>, formerly <spn>Leptops
olivaris</spn>) of the central U. S. having a flattened head and
projecting jaw.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flathead catfish, goujon, shovelnose catfish,
spoonbill catfish, <spn>Pylodictus olivaris</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

